  "title": "Être — to be",
  "es_title": "El verbo « être » (ser / estar)",
  "focus": "Your first French verb, wrapped in words you already own from Spanish.",
  "objectives": [
    "Conjugate être in the present (spoken forms).",
    "Use c'est and on like a real French speaker.",
    "Describe yourself and things using ~10 transparent cognate adjectives."
  ],
  "grammar": {
    "intro_es": "« être » es como ser/estar. El francés no separa ser y estar: un solo verbo cubre los dos. Fíjate: casi todo lo que lo acompaña aquí ya lo reconoces del español.",
    "conjugation": {
      "verb": "être", "en": "to be", "es": "ser / estar",
      "present": [
        {"pron": "je",           "form": "suis",   "ipa": "ʒə sɥi", "es": "(yo) soy / estoy",        "audio": "L01-c-je"},
        {"pron": "tu",           "form": "es",     "ipa": "ty ɛ",   "es": "(tú) eres / estás",        "audio": "L01-c-tu"},
        {"pron": "il / elle / on","form": "est",   "ipa": "il ɛ",   "es": "(él/ella) es / está",      "audio": "L01-c-il"},
        {"pron": "nous",         "form": "sommes", "ipa": "nu sɔm", "es": "(nosotros) somos / estamos","audio": "L01-c-nous"},
        {"pron": "vous",         "form": "êtes",   "ipa": "vu zɛt", "es": "(ustedes) son / están",    "audio": "L01-c-vous"},
        {"pron": "ils / elles",  "form": "sont",   "ipa": "il sɔ̃", "es": "(ellos) son / están",      "audio": "L01-c-ils"}
      ]
    },
    "spoken_notes": [
      "On = we, in everyday speech. « On est à Nice » (not « nous sommes »).",
      "C'est = it is / that is — the single most useful phrase in French. « C'est important. »",
      "Final consonants are silent: es, est → /ɛ/ (like ‘eh’). Only the vowel sounds.",
      "Liaison: vous êtes → « vou-ZETT », ils sont → « il-SON »."
    ]
  },
